= Fake Window =
#context: vop
#type: node

"""Simulates a window light source using a perspective camera-based UV projection."""

== Overview ==

Fake Window samples directional texture maps based on the camera view direction, producing the illusion of a window at render time without actual geometry. Inspired by Unity's Fake Window shader.

The node projects five directional maps (opposite, left, right, top, bottom) and selects the appropriate one based on the incident ray direction.

@parameters

Opposite Map 0:
    #id: opposite_map
    File path for the straight-on (opposite-facing) texture.

Left Side Map 1:
    #id: left_side_map
    File path for the left-facing texture.

Right Side Map 2:
    #id: right_side_map
    File path for the right-facing texture.

Top Map 3:
    #id: top_map
    File path for the top-facing texture.

Bottom Map 4:
    #id: bottom_map
    File path for the bottom-facing texture.

Source Color Space:
    #id: srccolorspace
    Color space of the input textures. `Automatic` detects from file metadata; `Linear` forces linear interpretation.

Depth:
    #id: depth
    Maximum depth value for the `inDepth` output.

@outputs

Texture Map Color (`clr`):
    RGB color sampled from the selected directional map.

Output 2 (`outUV`):
    Projected UV coordinates.

Output 1 (`id`):
    Integer ID of the selected face direction.

Transformed 3D Entity (`outNor`):
    Transformed normal vector.

Output 4 (`inDepth`):
    Depth value scaled by the Depth parameter.
